  21:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****   ==============================================================================
  22:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****                        ##### How to use this driver #####
  23:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****   ==============================================================================
  24:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****   [..]
  25:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****     This driver is a generic layered driver which contains a set of APIs used to
  26:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****     control SDRAM memories. It uses the FMC layer functions to interface
  27:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****     with SDRAM devices.
  28:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****     The following sequence should be followed to configure the FMC to interface
  29:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****     with SDRAM memories:
  30:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c **** 
  31:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****    (#) Declare a SDRAM_HandleTypeDef handle structure, for example:
  32:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****           SDRAM_HandleTypeDef  hsdram
  33:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c **** 
  34:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****        (++) Fill the SDRAM_HandleTypeDef handle "Init" field with the allowed
  35:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****             values of the structure member.
  36:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c **** 
  37:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****        (++) Fill the SDRAM_HandleTypeDef handle "Instance" field with a predefined
  38:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****             base register instance for NOR or SDRAM device
  39:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c **** 
  40:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****    (#) Declare a FMC_SDRAM_TimingTypeDef structure; for example:
  41:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****           FMC_SDRAM_TimingTypeDef  Timing;
  42:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****       and fill its fields with the allowed values of the structure member.
  43:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c **** 
  44:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****    (#) Initialize the SDRAM Controller by calling the function HAL_SDRAM_Init(). This function
  45:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****        performs the following sequence:
  46:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c **** 
  47:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****        (##) MSP hardware layer configuration using the function HAL_SDRAM_MspInit()
  48:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****        (##) Control register configuration using the FMC SDRAM interface function
  49:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****             FMC_SDRAM_Init()
  50:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****        (##) Timing register configuration using the FMC SDRAM interface function
  51:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****             FMC_SDRAM_Timing_Init()
  52:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****        (##) Program the SDRAM external device by applying its initialization sequence
  53:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****             according to the device plugged in your hardware. This step is mandatory
  54:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****             for accessing the SDRAM device.
  55:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c **** 
  56:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****    (#) At this stage you can perform read/write accesses from/to the memory connected
  57:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****        to the SDRAM Bank. You can perform either polling or DMA transfer using the
  58:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****        following APIs:
  59:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****        (++) HAL_SDRAM_Read()/HAL_SDRAM_Write() for polling read/write access
  60:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****        (++) HAL_SDRAM_Read_DMA()/HAL_SDRAM_Write_DMA() for DMA read/write transfer
  61:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c **** 
  62:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****    (#) You can also control the SDRAM device by calling the control APIs HAL_SDRAM_WriteOperation_E
  63:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****        HAL_SDRAM_WriteOperation_Disable() to respectively enable/disable the SDRAM write operation 
  64:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****        the function HAL_SDRAM_SendCommand() to send a specified command to the SDRAM
  65:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****        device. The command to be sent must be configured with the FMC_SDRAM_CommandTypeDef
  66:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****        structure.
  67:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c **** 
  68:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****    (#) You can continuously monitor the SDRAM device HAL state by calling the function
  69:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****        HAL_SDRAM_GetState()
  70:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c **** 
  71:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****    *** Callback registration ***
  72:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****     =============================================
  73:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****     [..]
  74:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****       The compilation define  USE_HAL_SDRAM_REGISTER_CALLBACKS when set to 1
  75:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****       allows the user to configure dynamically the driver callbacks.
  76:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c **** 
  77:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****       Use Functions HAL_SDRAM_RegisterCallback() to register a user callback,
ARM GAS  /tmp/cc5KvZM9.s 			page 3


  78:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****       it allows to register following callbacks:
  79:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****         (+) MspInitCallback    : SDRAM MspInit.
  80:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****         (+) MspDeInitCallback  : SDRAM MspDeInit.
  81:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****       This function takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle, the Callback ID
  82:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****       and a pointer to the user callback function.
  83:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c **** 
  84:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****       Use function HAL_SDRAM_UnRegisterCallback() to reset a callback to the default
  85:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****       weak (overridden) function. It allows to reset following callbacks:
  86:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****         (+) MspInitCallback    : SDRAM MspInit.
  87:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****         (+) MspDeInitCallback  : SDRAM MspDeInit.
  88:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****       This function) takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle and the Callback ID.
  89:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c **** 
  90:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****       By default, after the HAL_SDRAM_Init and if the state is HAL_SDRAM_STATE_RESET
  91:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****       all callbacks are reset to the corresponding legacy weak (overridden) functions.
  92:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****       Exception done for MspInit and MspDeInit callbacks that are respectively
  93:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****       reset to the legacy weak (overridden) functions in the HAL_SDRAM_Init
  94:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****       and  HAL_SDRAM_DeInit only when these callbacks are null (not registered beforehand).
  95:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****       If not, MspInit or MspDeInit are not null, the HAL_SDRAM_Init and HAL_SDRAM_DeInit
  96:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****       keep and use the user MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks (registered beforehand)
  97:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c **** 
  98:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****       Callbacks can be registered/unregistered in READY state only.
  99:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****       Exception done for MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks that can be registered/unregistered
 100:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****       in READY or RESET state, thus registered (user) MspInit/DeInit callbacks can be used
 101:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****       during the Init/DeInit.
 102:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****       In that case first register the MspInit/MspDeInit user callbacks
 103:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****       using HAL_SDRAM_RegisterCallback before calling HAL_SDRAM_DeInit
 104:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****       or HAL_SDRAM_Init function.
 105:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c **** 
 106:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****       When The compilation define USE_HAL_SDRAM_REGISTER_CALLBACKS is set to 0 or
 107:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****       not defined, the callback registering feature is not available
 108:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****       and weak (overridden) callbacks are used.
 109:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c **** 
 110:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_sdram.c ****   @endverbatim
